istians, conscious of the fact that they were metaphorically bearing Christ in their hearts. A later, over-literal interpretation of the name gave rise to the legend of a saint who actually bore the Christ-child over a stream; he is regarded as the patron of travellers. In England the name was uncommon in the Middle Ages, but became very popular in the 16th century, especially in parts of the North."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Katherine Maxwell was born in 1242, in Scotland. She married Herbert Maxwell 3rd Lord of Caerlaverock before 1262. They were the parents of at least 3 sons. She was buried in Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1242–":"1242–Surnud","1240–1298":"1240–1298","1262–1307":"1262–1307","1270–1311":"1270–1311","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1311":"1311","2 June 1262":"2. juuni 1262","1298":"1298","1242":"1242","before 1262":"enne 1262","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1307":"1307","Caerlaverock Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1242–":"1242–Kuollut","1240–1298":"1240–1298","1262–1307":"1262–1307","1270–1311":"1270–1311","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1311":"1311","2 June 1262":"2. kesäkuuta 1262","1298":"1298","1242":"1242","before 1262":"ennen vuotta 1262","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1307":"1307","Caerlaverock Castle, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fr":{"1242–":"1242–Décédée","1240–1298":"1240–1298","1262–1307":"1262–1307","1270–1311":"1270–1311","1242–Female":"1242–Décédée","1311":"1311","2 June 1262":"2 juin 1262","1298":"1298","1242":"1242","before 1262":"avant 1262","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","1270":"1270","1307":"1307","Caerlaverock 